# DevFlow ephemeral working state (review caches, weekly-loop temp files).
# Ignore everything under .devflow/ EXCEPT the committed overrides/templates
# below. (Use /.devflow/* — not /.devflow/ — so the negations can re-include;
# a wholesale dir-ignore can't be overridden per-path.)
/.devflow/*
!/.devflow/learnings/
# Committed config template + schema (shipped). The LIVE .devflow/config.json
# is NOT listed here, so it stays ignored — each adopter creates their own
# (it holds project/board IDs). Force-add with `git add -f` to dogfood DevFlow
# on this very repo and have its cloud workflows read it.
!/.devflow/config.example.json
!/.devflow/config.schema.json
# Shipped per-language tool/preset registry read by scripts/detect-project-tools.sh
# (/devflow:init). Must be tracked so the plugin ships it and a clean checkout works.
!/.devflow/tool-presets.json
/.devflow-scratch/
/.devflow-tmp/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/

# OS / editor
.DS_Store
*.swp
# WSL/Windows download marker (alternate data stream) — appears on any file.
*:Zone.Identifier

# Private maintainer working docs — never publish (kept outside the repo).
/devflow-roadmap.md
*.private.md
